data.title: Our Team – Boyd Watterson
data.text:
Brian Gevry, CFA

Brian L. Gevry, CFA, is the Chief Executive Officer and Co-Chief Investment Officer of Boyd Watterson, responsible for the strategic leadership of the company and oversight of the company’s investment processes and committees. As CEO, he focuses on the development and execution of the firm’s vision, cultural values, goals, and strategies, allocating resources as necessary to meet client needs while achieving the long-term success of the organization. As Co-CIO, his focus is guiding the investment process, including developing investment philosophy and procedures to ensure Boyd Watterson delivers investment results that meet client expectations while maintaining moderate levels of risk.

Brian joined Boyd Watterson’s predecessor firm, Duff & Phelps Investment Management, in November of 1991. Prior to becoming CEO and CIO in 2006, Brian held various management positions including Chief Operating Officer and Deputy CIO. His approach to leadership reflects his personal philosophy which is centered around honesty and integrity. Brian has worked to shape the organization’s foundational culture, emphasizing inclusivity and transparency, to ensure all employees understand and demonstrate Boyd Watterson’s values and beliefs.

Additionally, Brian established the Strategic Management Process, through which he sets and oversees long-term company and line of business objectives. He has been instrumental in the company’s growth, more than doubling AUM over the last five years. This growth continues to accelerate with expanded asset classes and new product offerings comprising real estate, fixed income, and equity. Throughout his tenure as CEO, Brian has expanded Boyd Watterson’s national footprint, opening offices in Bloomfield Hills, MI, Washington, D.C., Tampa, FL, Denver, CO, and most recently, West Hartford, CT, to join the already-established headquarters in Cleveland, OH, and office in Chicago, IL.

MBA from Case Western Reserve University

BA from Cleveland State University

CFA Charter Holder

Member of the CFA Institute

Member of the CFA Society of Cleveland

Chair of the Cleveland State University Foundation Investment Committee

Member of the Cleveland State Visiting Committee for the College of Arts and Science

Member of the Schott Memorial Center Foundation, Inc.

Member of the Open Door Christian Schools Board

Member of the National Symphony Orchestra Board of Directors

Timothy Hyland

Timothy M. Hyland is on the Committee of Managers for Boyd Watterson Asset Management and is President of the company. Additionally, Tim is the National Director of Sales, Marketing, and Client Service. He is responsible for setting the strategic direction of the Distribution and Marketing teams, formulating annual plans, and overseeing their implementation. It is through his passion for client service and determination to meet client expectations that he maintains and grows existing relationships with consultants and institutions and creates new relationships. Tim is also focused on monitoring market trends in order to provide insight in the development of marketing materials and new products.

Tim’s relationship with Boyd Watterson began in October of 1994 when he joined the predecessor firm Duff and Phelps Investment Management Co. as Executive Vice President and National Sales Manager. Under his leadership, the firm has significantly expanded relationships, as well as assets under management, and has established a strong national presence.

Prior to joining Duff & Phelps in 1994, Tim was a Senior Vice President at McDonald & Co. Securities, Inc., earning a prestigious distinction in the firm’s Presidents’ Council for top producers.

BS from the Georgia Institute of Technology

Brian Convery, CFA

Brian A. Convery, CFA, is the Co-Chief Investment Officer of Boyd Watterson. Together with the Chief Executive Officer, Brian is responsible for guiding the investment process and developing investment philosophy and procedures to ensure Boyd Watterson delivers investment results that meet client expectations while maintaining moderate levels of risk. He leads, alongside the CEO, the Macro and Investment Policy Committees, focusing on evaluating the broad investment market and guiding risk and return positioning.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in 2011, Brian had an extensive career highlighted by roles including management consultant focusing on corporate strategy, and investment analyst specializing in high-yield bonds. His initial role with Boyd was Portfolio Manager of Credit Research. His initiative and innovation quickly elevated his position to his current role, advising on strategic direction and facilitating new product development and execution. Within the real estate division, Brian serves as a portfolio manager and member of the Investment Committee. He was instrumental in the development and launch of the firm’s state and local government focused open-ended real estate fund and open-ended REIT product and is an integral part of new product development. He has also driven the development and growth of the Research and Data Lab, a facet of the company focusing on qualitative and quantitative decision making, which he now directs.

MBA from Georgetown University

BA from the University of Dayton

CFA Charterholder

Member of the CFA Institute

Member of the CFA Society of Cleveland

Patty Jamieson

Patricia J. Jamieson is Chief Financial Officer and is responsible for the oversight of the Finance, Accounting, Human Resources, and Administration departments for the company. Patricia works closely with the CEO and other executives in setting strategic direction and determining long-term and annual line of business objectives. She is dedicated to optimizing productivity and progress by ensuring human capital and systems resources are in place, in order to drive the strategic goals.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in March of 2016, Patricia built an extensive resume in the financial services sector, including fifteen years as an executive at Keycorp. Her roles included CFO of the Corporate Bank and the Director of Planning & Performance Management. Patricia continues to display her commitment and initiative at Boyd Watterson, driving efficiency and process improvement throughout the company.

BS in Accounting from John Carroll University

Michael Bee

Michael E. Bee serves on the Committee of Managers for Boyd Watterson Asset Management. He is responsible for providing excellent service and recommending income solutions to clients and prospective clients. He also reviews trends within the institutional marketplace to assist the portfolio management team in the development of new products. Additionally, Michael serves as an equity strategist and portfolio manager, overseeing the company’s equity assets under management.

Michael has expertise in several areas of the business dating back to when he began his career in October of 1990 with Boyd’s predecessor, Duff & Phelps Investment Management Co. He has served in various roles over the years and has remained ever focused on the client.

MBA from John Carroll University

Graduate Studies at the University of Chicago

BS in Economics from DePaul University

Member of Laurel School Investment Committee

Member of Kibble Pet Co. Board

Michael Vandenbossche, CFA

As the Chief Investment Officer for Fixed Income, Michael R. Vandenbossche, CFA, focuses on investment strategy formation and portfolio management of Boyd Watterson’s Fixed Income line of business. Responsible for ensuring investments follow client guidelines, with the goal of realizing client objectives and outperforming applicable benchmarks and competitor peer groups, while managing downside risks. He oversees the daily execution and implementation of the investment process. Mike started with the company in October of 2014 as a Senior Portfolio Manager before transitioning into his current role as CIO.

Previously, Mike served as a Portfolio Manager with Ambassador Capital Management and Munder Capital Management, where he was a member of the Investment Strategy team, headed the Captive Insurance team, and managed the corporate and CMBS sectors. His resume also includes time at Victory Capital Management and First of America Bank in such roles as Portfolio Manager, Asset/Liability Manager, and Municipal Analyst.

MBA from Western Michigan University

BA in Finance from Central Michigan University

CFA Charterholder

Member of the CFA Institute

Member of the CFA Society of Detroit

Robert Law

Robert Law is Co-Chief Investment Officer of the real estate division and is responsible, together with the CO-CIOs, to drive the execution of investment processes. He focuses on the development, maintenance, and oversight of real estate investment strategies and products to effectively monitor performance and risk management. Further, he mentors real estate team members across the company in order to transfer his deep real estate knowledge. In collaboration with the Chief Executive Officer, Bob guides the real estate team in the development and execution of long-term and tactical business plans.

Bob joined Boyd Watterson in May of 2009 with deep roots in the real estate sector. He spent 14 years as the Managing Director of Real Estate Investment Management at the Mercantile Bank and Trust Company in Baltimore. During that time, he grew the AFL-CIO’s Building Investment Trust from $200 million to $1.9 billion over a 10-year period. His career has spanned more than three decades and is highlighted at Boyd Watterson by his close involvement in the establishment of the real estate line of business and subsequent real estate funds and programs.

BS in Civil Engineering from the Virginia Military Institute

Attended the Graduate Government and Business program at George Washington University

Thomas Tarantino

Thomas J. Tarantino is Chief Operating Officer, Chief Legal Officer and Chief Compliance Officer and is responsible for the management of the day-to-day operations of the company, including the technology and human resource teams. He also oversees the Legal department and regulatory compliance function, including internal legal and compliance personnel. In addition, Thomas manages the investor relations and new product implementation teams.

Thomas joined Boyd Watterson in January of 2016 and played an integral role in the establishment and growth of the internal Legal department, as well as the expansion of compliance processes and practices, keeping pace with company growth and increasing regulatory demands. Thomas has also supervised the creation of the new product implementation group and dedicated investor relations team. He has more than 25 years of law experience focusing on such areas as corporate and business law, investment adviser regulation, securities law, commercial real estate, government law, and public finance.

JD from Cleveland-Marshall College of Law

BA from Cleveland State University

Admitted to the Supreme Court of Ohio, the United States District Court, Northern District of Ohio and the United States Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit

Currently serving on the Board of Directors of Deepwood Foundation

Member of the National Society of Compliance Professionals and various bar associations

James Waler

James A. Waler is the Chief Technology Officer and is responsible for constructing, evaluating, and optimizing Boyd Watterson’s technology infrastructure and framework. He works closely with the CEO and key executives to identify and implement the best technologies and services to meet strategic long-term objectives. James also provides oversight and guidance to the IT and Operations departments, ensuring systems and practices are in place for customer security and satisfaction.

James began working for Boyd Watterson in July of 1990 when it was under the name of its predecessor, Duff & Phelps Management Co. James has been a critical component in the creation of proprietary systems throughout the company and in streamlining and enhancing processes and procedures.

BS in Computer Science from John Carroll University

Casey Wendeln

Casey F. Wendeln is the Deputy CIO of the Real Estate division. He serves as the primary portfolio manager for the Boyd Watterson state and local government focused real estate fund and a secondary portfolio manager for the Boyd Waterson GSA focused open-end real estate fund. In these roles, he is responsible for the monitoring and oversight of all activities of the funds, including acquisition and disposition activity, asset management and leasing, balance sheet and capital markets activities, and client relations and reporting. Casey is the Co-Head of Asset Management and Head of the Boyd Watterson Chicago office. He provides oversight for the LIFE fund and separate account activities. In addition, Casey is a member of the Real Estate Investment Committee, Allocation Committee, Finance Committee, and chairs the Underwriting Committee.

Casey began his career with the company in 2009 and was an instrumental part of building the Real Estate Investment team and its investment vehicles from the ground up. Prior to joining Boyd Watterson, Casey was an Associate in the Capital Markets Group at Jones Lang LaSalle in Chicago, working on $2.4 billion in investment sales of office, industrial, and retail properties nationwide.

MBA from the Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University

BBA in Finance from the University of Notre Dame, magna cum laude

ULI member

PREA member

CREPE member

Kellogg Real Estate Alumni Club member

Active fund-raiser for the Alzheimer’s Association

Coach at the youth sports level for multiple teams

Zachary Segal

As Co-Deputy Chief Investment Officer of the Real Estate team, Zachary L. Segal focuses on investment activities, product development, and strategic initiatives. Zach is Co-Portfolio Manager of the open-ended REIT product and a member of the Real Estate Investment and Allocation Committees. Additionally, Zach focuses on the research, proposal, and launch of new products.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in April of 2022, Zach was a Partner and Special Situations Group Director of Asset Management at The Townsend Group, executing and managing real estate private equity investments across property types, markets, and structures. Zach also held real estate finance and principal investing roles at Polinger Development Co., Goldman, Sachs & Co., and Charles River Realty Investors, LLC. During the global financial crisis, Zach served as Director of Strategic Initiatives and Credit Market Programs at the U.S. Department of the Treasury, where he managed Troubled Asset Relief Program (TARP) investments.

MBA from the Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth

BA in English from Dartmouth College, cum laude

Kathleen Herrin

As Chief Financial Officer for the Real Estate Funds, Kathleen B. Herrin is responsible for the accounting, finance, cash management, and external audit functions for the Boyd Watterson Real Estate funds and programs. Kathy ensures that each accounting function and report is completed accurately and timely, providing meaningful analysis. She maintains relationships with third-party fund administrators, auditors, and banking institutions, and provides direction, mentoring, and training to her team. Kathy has built and continues to improve processes that result in efficient and effective completion of the many required deliverables.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in December of 2010, Kathy served as a Vice President, Controller, and Asset Manager for a boutique Chicago real estate investment firm where she was responsible for overseeing the accounting and finance functions for real estate investment accounts. Kathy has extensive experience in all aspects of real estate accounting and finance, having also worked in management positions at ORIX Real Estate Equities and Lasalle Partners.

BS in Accounting with a concentration in Finance from the University of Illinois at Chicago

Stephen Perry

Stephen A. Perry sits on the Board of Directors for Boyd Watterson Asset Management. In addition, he serves in the capacity of a Strategic Advisor within the company. In his role as Strategic Advisor, Stephen facilitates the Strategic Management Process through which the CEO manages the firm and develops long-term and line of business objectives, ensuring goals and action plans are specific and measurable. He is also a member of the Real Estate Investment Committee, where he assists in the review of potential property acquisitions and provides insight into the government space.

Since joining Boyd Watterson in January of 2015, Stephen has helped guide the company through a period of extreme growth, thanks in part to his results-oriented personality and diligence. Stephen’s extensive career includes roles as the President of the Pro Football Hall of Fame, the 17th Administrator (CEO) for the U.S. General Services Administration (GSA), the Director of the Department of Administrative Services for the State of Ohio, and Senior Vice President of Human Resources at Timken Company.

MS in Management from Stanford University

BS in Accounting from the University of Akron

Executive Management Program – University of Michigan Graduate School of Business Administration, Ann Arbor, Michigan

Al Iudicello

Al Iudicello is a Strategic Advisor to the real estate team focused on establishing acquisition strategy, particularly in the GSA National Capital Region (“NCR”). He is a consultant to the Acquisitions team and is responsible for leveraging his extensive expertise to advise on acquisitions and lease renewal negotiations in accordance with investment strategy and policy guidelines. Al maintains relationships with industry experts, including relevant government officials, developers, and owners.

Al joined Boyd Watterson in January of 2017 after serving as CEO of NGP I-V. He has led an emphasis on the NCR, which has resulted in a major presence for Boyd Watterson. Additionally, Al participates in a variety of product development initiatives, one of which was Boyd Watterson’s second private open-end real estate fund, launched in 2018.

Graduate of the U.S. Air Force Academy

Executive MBA from Georgetown University

MCE from Catholic University

Thomas Cicotello

Thomas M. Cicotello is a Portfolio Manager in the real estate division and is responsible for developing and maintaining key strategic relationships with real estate owners, developers, brokers, government staff, civic leaders, and other partners, and for establishing a pipeline of acquisitions for the Boyd Watterson real estate programs.

In January of 2018, Tom joined Boyd Watterson and led the opening of the company’s office in Washington, D.C. His role has since elevated to Head of the D.C. office, where he embodies and maintains Boyd Watterson culture and values. Most recently, he guided the opening of Boyd Watterson’s newest office in Denver, Colorado.

Prior to joining Boyd, Thomas was a Senior Asset Manager and Director of Commercial Leasing for the privately held Clark Enterprises, Inc. (CEI) of Bethesda, Md., where he was responsible for the oversight of management, leasing, and capital improvement activities associated with CEI’s commercial and hospitality portfolio.

BSBA in International Business and Finance from the American University

CCIM from the CCIM Institute

RPA from the Building Owners and Managers Institute International

Monsignor Smyth Endowment Fund Board Member

SW Business Improvement District in Washington Board Member

NoMa Business Improvement District in Washington, DC Board Member

Timothy Horne

Timothy O. Horne is a Portfolio Manager in the real estate division and Head of the Denver, Colorado office. He is responsible for ongoing management of the GSA focused open-end real estate fund, the maintenance and continued growth of the company’s investment footprint throughout the western third of the United States, and for developing and maintaining key strategic relationships. Tim provides senior level support and guidance for the Colorado team, personifying and maintaining Boyd Watterson culture and values.

Tim’s resume includes a long tenure with the General Services Administration where, prior to joining Boyd Watterson in February of 2021, he was Regional Commissioner of the Public Buildings Service for GSA’s Region 8 and Acting Administrator of GSA. His extensive career in the government space provides a solid framework for his contribution to Boyd’s vast government leased real estate portfolios.

BS in Finance from Regis University

BA in Communications from Regis University

Member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Committee

Timothy Walsh

Timothy D. Walsh is a Portfolio Manager within Boyd’s real estate division and is based out of Connecticut. He is responsible for managing, along with the Co-Portfolio Manager, the firm’s open-ended REIT product. He works to develop and execute strategies to grow and maintain the REIT, while also optimizing returns through asset allocation and selection and process improvements. Tim also works on special initiatives across the real estate division.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in July of 2023, Tim spent 17 years of his career at UBS Asset Management as a Managing Director, member of the Investment and Management Committees, and Senior Portfolio Manager for the firm’s open-end, core-plus fund. He also spent a decade in acquisitions, closing more than $2.5 billion in fee simple, joint venture, and participating mortgage transactions across all property types and all major Northeast and Southeast markets. Tim’s diverse experience also includes eight years in property management, development, and construction in Southern California, Las Vegas, and Chicago.

MBA from the Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth

BA in English at Amherst College

Volunteer for the Ron Foley Foundation for Pancreatic Cancer Research

Foster for the New England Puppy Rescue

Brian Orr

Brian R. Orr is a Portfolio Manager across the real estate products, focusing primarily on GSA/ federal leased properties and is responsible for deeply understanding all aspects of those assets. He has a thorough understanding of asset and portfolio risks and works with the portfolio team to develop appropriate mitigation strategies to actively identify opportunities for improving portfolio performance. He is further responsible for communicating his expertise internally to assist in the strategic management of the real estate programs, and externally to provide transparency to investors. Further, Brian is responsible for maintaining relationships with developers, owners, brokers, and other real estate professionals.

Brian came to Boyd Watterson in July of 2014 from Ernst & Young, LLP where he managed a team on various investment consulting, valuation, and capital markets engagements for the Transaction Real Estate Advisory Services group. While at Boyd, Brian has remained focused on driving the total return for the company’s GSA focused open-end real estate fund.

BA from Purdue University

Member of Chicago Real Estate Council

Member of Mortgage Bankers Association

Associate member of the Institute of Real Estate Managements

Volunteer for Nourishing Hope

Volunteer for Chicago Lights Urban Farm program

Kristen Albano

Kristen L. Albano is a Portfolio Manager across the real estate products, focusing primarily on the state and local government leased properties while also concentrating on asset-specific strategies, portfolio composition objectives, and liability management. Kristen makes frequent site visits in order to understand the assets, markets, and owners where the funds are invested so she may actively identify opportunities for portfolio improvement and assist the firm with the acquisition of additional assets. She serves as an active communication conduit between the asset and product portfolio management teams, while also strengthening client-facing interaction and consultant relationships.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in July of 2014, Kristen worked at IndCor Properties, a Blackstone-owned company, as a Manager within the Finance Group. Kristen began her career with Boyd as an Asset Manager and held positions with ever-increasing responsibilities, leading to her current role in portfolio management.

MBA in Finance and Real Estate from the University of San Diego

BS in Policy Analysis and Management from Cornell University

Christopher Ried

Christopher G. Ried is a Chief Financial Officer for the Real Estate Funds responsible for overseeing the accounting functions for the company’s real estate products. He ensures the accurate and timely completion of related financial reports, manages external vendors that provide accounting and fund administration, and assists the Real Estate team with preparing meaningful financial analysis, forecasting, and budgeting in order to enhance investor return.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in October 2021, Chris served as a Senior Manager at RSM where he worked on financial statement audits of real estate companies, including property joint ventures, private equity funds, and separate accounts.

MSA from the University of Illinois – Urbana-Champaign

BS in Accountancy from the University of Illinois – Urbana-Champaign

Certified Public Accountant

Evan Yerega

Evan M. Yerega oversees the strategy and execution of all financing activities for Boyd Watterson’s real estate funds and programs as Treasurer. His responsibilities include managing all banking and lender relationships and directing all hedging activities, as well as sourcing and negotiating all secured and unsecured credit lines. Additionally, he chairs the Real Estate Financing Advisory Group.

Evan started with Boyd Waterson in July of 2019 and has greatly expanded the ability of Boyd Watterson’s real estate funds and programs to obtain competitively priced financing. Previously, he was employed with KeyCorp for more than 10 years, holding various roles of increasing responsibility within the Finance, Treasury, Credit Risk, and Commercial Real Estate groups. Most recently, he worked in Key’s Income Property Group where he managed a portfolio of project loans across property types.

BBA in Finance and Economics from Ohio University

Eric Dowling

Eric F. Dowling is the Head of Acquisitions for GSA/federal leased properties. He manages a team of professionals focused on the sourcing, underwriting, negotiating, and closing of real estate investments across the federal-leased sector that meet the investment criteria determined in concert with the Portfolio Management team. He is responsible for developing and maintaining key relationships with real estate owners, developers, brokers, and government staff to ensure Boyd Watterson’s significance in the space and for establishing a pipeline of acquisitions to meet investor needs.

Eric joined Boyd Watterson in July of 2015 with several years of development, underwriting, acquisitions, and asset management experience to his credit. He has made a significant impact in the rapid growth of Boyd’s real estate funds and programs.

MBA with a concentration in Real Estate from the University of Wisconsin-Madison

BS in Business Administration from Villanova University

Joseph Capra

Joseph V. Capra is Head of Acquisitions for state and local government leased properties. He manages a team of professionals who source, negotiate, underwrite, and close on real estate assets leased to state, county, and municipal governments nationwide. Joe is responsible for executing the strategy to deliver income-focused returns to investors. He is also an instrumental part of the company’s structured financing efforts, negotiating numerous joint venture agreements, forward commitments, and mezzanine loans. While at Boyd, Joe has been a large part of the growth of the GSA focused open-end real estate fund as well as growing assets in the state and local government focused real estate fund since its inception.

Joe has more than 28 years of experience in real estate principal investing, investment banking, commercial real estate lending, and financial markets. Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in October of 2015, Joe was the Director of the Midwest Capital Markets Group at DTZ (now Cushman & Wakefield).

MBA with a concentration in Finance from the University of Missouri

BS in Business Administration with a concentration in Finance from Truman State University

Nicholas Nigro

Nicholas M. Nigro is Head of Acquisitions for Boyd Watterson’s first open-end real estate REIT. He oversees a team of professionals focused on sourcing, underwriting, managing, and closing acquisitions anchored by government contractors and other quasi-government agencies across asset classes. Nicholas has an attention to detail fine-tuned through more than a decade of institutional real estate experience that is invaluable to the due diligence process. Nicholas works closely with the Portfolio Management team to acquire assets that fit investment criteria, while establishing and cultivating relationships with brokers, investors, lenders, and other market participants.

He joined the firm in February of 2021, previously serving as a Director at Bridge Investment Group where he oversaw Midwest regional acquisitions and the asset management of a 2.3 million square foot value-add office portfolio. He also worked at Argentic Investment Management, a New York-based affiliate of Elliott Capital Management, where he managed the underwriting, due diligence, and closing of debt investments across asset classes.

BS in Finance and Accounting from Boston College

Member of NAIOP Industrial & Office Trends Forum

Francis Coppola

As Regional Director of Asset Management for the Eastern region, Frank Coppola is responsible for overseeing the asset managers of properties located in the East. He works with his team to ensure portfolio performance, focusing on maximizing return while mitigating risk.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in June of 2019, Frank was a Portfolio Manager with Lincoln Property Company where he oversaw real estate assets in southwest Washington D.C. He also served as a Group Manager, Vice President, and Team Leader with JLL, managing all financial and operational aspects within a portfolio of properties in the DC Metropolitan Area.

BS in Business Administration from Susquehanna University

CCIM designation from the Realtors National Marketing Institute

State of Maryland Associate Broker License

LEED Green Associate

Della Wegman

Della G. Wegman is the Regional Director of Asset Management for the Western region, responsible for overseeing the regional asset managers, providing guidance and expertise. Della works with her team to maximize return and mitigate risk within the portfolio of assets they manage by focusing on lease renewal, expense management, and hold/sell analysis.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in March of 2021, Della was a Managing Director of the Central United States Asset Management for EverWest Real Estate Advisors, where she oversaw the investment performance of a portfolio valued at $1 billion. She also served as a Senior Vice President at Amstar Group, managing assets throughout the United States on behalf of a private family and public pension fund clients.

MBA from Drake University

BBA in Management Sciences from the University of Iowa

LEED-EB

Ryan Zader

Ryan A. Zader is the Regional Director of Asset Management for the Central region, responsible for overseeing a team of asset managers, providing guidance and expertise. Ryan works with his team to maximize returns and mitigate risk within the portfolio, focusing on lease execution, relationship management, operational & financial reporting, valuations, and dispositions to achieve fund objectives.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in May of 2023, Ryan was a Senior Vice President at CP Group, responsible for leading the firm’s acquisition and disposition efforts in the Denver & Phoenix markets. He was also responsible for the oversight of property management, construction management, leasing, and all other asset management-related functions in those markets.

BA in Economics with an emphasis in Real Estate Finance and Macroeconomics from the University of Michigan

Hugh Nisbet

Hugh K. Nisbet works on the Acquisitions team and is responsible for maintaining a robust pipeline and procuring properties for Boyd Watterson’s state and local government focused open-end real estate fund. He focuses on sourcing and analyzing potential properties which adhere to the investment guidelines and are portfolio enhancing, maximizing investor return and minimizing risk.

Hugh joined the firm in January of 2017 and was a member of the Boyd Watterson team that launched the second private open-end real estate fund. Prior to coming on board, he was a Senior Underwriter at KeyBank where he was responsible for the CMBS and Fannie Mae loans. His 23-plus years of experience in financial services also includes serving as a consultant at a variety of financial institutions in which he focused on evaluating risk associated with loan portfolios.

MBA in Finance from the University of Missouri

BSBA in Finance from the University of Missouri

LEED Green Associate

Trenton Joyce

Trenton M. Joyce is part of the Acquisitions team and is responsible primarily for deal evaluation. He performs underwriting analysis, due diligence assessments, data gathering, market analysis, and tenant research to ensure prospective acquisitions meet investment criteria as determined by the portfolio management team.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in January of 2018, Trent was a Commercial Mortgage Analyst for Fitch Ratings where he assessed credit characteristics of U.S. and Canadian Commercial Mortgage-Backed Securities (CMBS) with average asset-values of $1 billion by investigating legal documents, analyzing historical financial statements, and evaluating economic, demographic, and real estate market data. He also served as a Structured Finance Analyst for US Bank where he built and maintained Mortgage-Backed Security (MBS) and Asset-Backed Security (ABS) waterfall distribution models.

BBA in Finance from the University of Dayton

Currently enrolled in the CFA Program

LEED Green Associate

Daniel Orcutt

Daniel A. Orcutt is an Asset Manager on the Real Estate team in the Washington, D.C., office. Dan manages a portfolio of assets in Washington, D.C., Virginia, Maryland, and New York City with an emphasis on minimizing risks, maximizing returns, and continually monitoring performance. He is relationship focused, ensuring client, tenant, and leasing stakeholders needs are met. He maintains close oversight of property management and leasing functions performed by service partners, performs financial analysis, and reviews valuations.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in September of 2021, Dan accumulated nearly 30 years of experience in the industry serving in such positions as the mid-Atlantic market leader and Director of Management Services at Newmark, as well as Director at CBRE, where he was responsible for a portfolio consisting of 10 million square feet of office and industrial assets throughout the Washington Metro area.

BA in Environmental Design from the University at Buffalo

Certified Property Manager (CPM) from the Institute of Real Estate Management (IREM)

LEED Green Associate

Christopher Winn

Christopher E. Winn is an Asset Manager for the real estate team located in the Denver, CO, office. He is responsible for a portfolio of real estate assets in the Western Region. His proactive approach helps him obtain tenant retention, asset preservation and improvement, and maximum returns. Chris directs all aspects of managing the properties, including administration, operation, and financial oversight.

Before joining Boyd Watterson in September 2021, Chris compiled 18 years of experience within the industry serving in such positions as Director of Asset Management at Everwest Real Estate Investors and Asset Manager for Consolidated Investment Group, where he managed a portfolio of industrial, office, and multi-family properties.

MBA in Finance from the University of Wisconsin-Madison

BS in Geology from the University of California, Santa Barbara

LEED Green Associate

Steve Riley

Within the Asset Management team, Steve Riley oversees a portfolio of real estate properties, focusing on maximizing lease potential, minimizing risk, and continually monitoring performance. He works closely with property managers, agency officials, and tenants to ensure needs are being met, oversees all property management functions performed by third-party vendors, and reviews budgets, financial packages, and valuations.

Before joining Boyd Watterson in September 2019, Steve served as a Senior Associate in Jones Lang LaSalle’s Capital Markets Division, focusing on government related and institutional investment sales as a part of more than $750 million in transactions. Steve also worked at Brandywine Realty Trust and First Potomac Realty Trust where he focused on asset management, transactions, and development activities.

BSBA with a focus in Real Estate from the University of Central Florida

LEED Green Associate

Ryan Gerrety

As a real estate asset management team member, Ryan P. Gerrety oversees the operation of a portfolio of properties, primarily located in the East region. He is responsible for managing capital expenditures, maximizing potential for lease renewal, maintaining physical integrity of the properties by oversight of property management teams, and staying informed of market trends in order to mitigate risk and pursue additional value.

Prior to joining Boyd Watterson in February 2020, Ryan was a Real Estate Manager with CBRE where he managed all aspects of various assets in Washington D.C. and Virginia, including day-to-day operations, annual budgeting, and capital project planning. Additionally, he worked as an Account Executive with CoStar Group in Washington D.C. where he was responsible for sales of the company’s suite of products.

BA in Political Science from Elon University

LEED Green Associate

Jesse Meetre

As a member of the real estate asset management team, Jesse J. Meetre is responsible for the oversight and performance of a portfolio of assets, primarily in the East region. He works to maximize return while minimizing risk by working closely with property managers and tenants to obtain lease renewals, maintaining the physical integrity of each asset, managing NOI and cash flow, and overseeing valuations.

Part of the Boyd Watterson team since March 2020, Jesse has managed various capital projects resulting in significant savings, in addition to successfully maintaining NOI through managing expenses. Previously, Jesse served as a Senior Associate, Asset Management for Carr Properties, as well as a Senior Analyst, Portfolio Management for First Potomac Realty Trust.

BSBA from the University of Central Florida

LEED Green Associate

Eshaan Varma

As an Asset Manager, Eshaan Varma oversees a portfolio of real estate holdings and works to achieve return objectives within set risk parameters. He partners with property managers to ensure the efficiency of property operations and to maintain the physical integrity of the assets. Additionally, Eshaan collaborates with leasing brokers to attract tenants and builds relationships at the tenant level, maximizing potential for lease renewal.
